        characters: ["Tipu Sultan (Tiger of Mysore)", "Lord Wellesley", "General George Harris", "Arthur Wellesley (future Duke of Wellington)"],
        details: "The final and catastrophic siege of Tipu Sultan's island capital of Seringapatam, which ended the Fourth Anglo-Mysore War. A massive British and allied Indian force of 50,000 surrounded and besieged the island fortress. Tipu Sultan had fewer than 30,000 defenders. The British systematically bombarded the walls for weeks until a practicable breach was created. In the final assault on 4 May, the British stormed the breach. Tipu Sultan, refusing any surrender, reportedly died with a sword in his hand fighting the British troops in the water gate. His body was found among the dead hours later, still unrecognized.",
